WEBVTT

00:02.500 --> 00:05.572
Tickets this way
for the Chatsworth Express!

00:05.660 --> 00:08.173
Come and watch pikeys making a mess

00:08.260 --> 00:11.855
of the lives they were given by
'im upstairs...

00:11.940 --> 00:14.898
And kids they're convinced
aren't actually theirs.

00:14.980 --> 00:16.094
Wicked!

00:16.180 --> 00:17.499
Piss off!

00:17.580 --> 00:21.368
What sounds on Earth
could ever replace

00:21.460 --> 00:24.497
kids needing money
or wives in your face?

00:24.580 --> 00:26.935
Cos this, people reckon -
me included -

00:27.020 --> 00:29.488
is why pubs and drugs

00:29.580 --> 00:31.172
were kindly invented...

00:31.260 --> 00:33.774
To calm us all down
and stop us going mental.

00:33.860 --> 00:38.570
These are Chatsworth Estate's
basic essentials.

00:38.660 --> 00:44.815
We are worth every penny
for grinding your axes...

00:44.900 --> 00:46.379
You sit on our head,

00:46.460 --> 00:49.133
but... you pay the taxes.

00:49.220 --> 00:50.619
CHEERING

00:50.700 --> 00:53.373
Imagine Britain
without Chatsworth buccaneers

00:53.460 --> 00:56.691
who'd come on your face
for the price of a beer, eh?

00:56.780 --> 00:58.259
Eh!

00:58.340 --> 01:02.094
Make poverty history.
Cheaper drugs now!

01:02.180 --> 01:07.049
Make poverty history!
Cheaper drugs now!

01:07.140 --> 01:08.459
CHUCKLES

01:08.540 --> 01:12.169
Scatter! Party!

01:15.660 --> 01:19.619
(Liam) 'Affairs of the heart
are troublesome to adults.

01:20.580 --> 01:23.378
'They're complex,
and carry lots of baggage.

01:23.460 --> 01:26.179
'And consequences. Big and small.'

01:26.260 --> 01:29.377
Will you fuckin' lie at peace?

01:29.460 --> 01:34.011
'It's the one area of life where adults
get to behave irrationally.

01:34.100 --> 01:35.897
'Like kids on a sugar rush,

01:35.980 --> 01:39.575
'tears and tantrums,
falling out and not speakin'.

01:39.660 --> 01:41.412
'Secrets and lies.

01:43.020 --> 01:45.170
'Makes you wonder whether it's worth it,

01:45.260 --> 01:48.491
'if it wouldn't it be better
to stay on your own?

01:48.580 --> 01:51.617
'Be a priest,
or a Trappist monk or somethin'?

01:51.700 --> 01:54.260
'Live apart from society?

01:56.340 --> 02:00.299
'lf only there was a superior being
I could believe in.'

02:05.940 --> 02:06.895
Where's Liam?

02:08.139 --> 02:10.973
He's gonna be late. Liam!

02:11.060 --> 02:13.494
Oh, don't get up, I'll fix his toast(!)

02:13.580 --> 02:15.935
Hello! Have you seen the size of me?

02:16.020 --> 02:17.214
FOOTSTEPS

02:17.300 --> 02:19.211
- You didn't wake me!
- Got a study day.

02:20.660 --> 02:23.049
MONICA LAUGHS

02:23.140 --> 02:27.019
God, he looks like
a refugee from the 1980s!

02:27.100 --> 02:29.170
There's nothing wrong with him.

02:29.260 --> 02:32.093
Well, the fashion police
might beg to differ, Debbie!

02:32.180 --> 02:33.533
Why's she laughin'?

02:33.620 --> 02:37.374
Cos her hormones have affected
her brain. Go and get your bag.

02:39.020 --> 02:42.569
Scar him for life, sending him
into school with trousers like that!

02:42.660 --> 02:45.254
They're gonna have to do him
till the end of term,

02:45.340 --> 02:47.490
unless you have a contribution to make.

02:47.580 --> 02:51.459
Oh, I forgot, he's my job,
just like everything else round here.

02:51.540 --> 02:54.293
Developing a victim complex,
are we, Debbie?

02:54.380 --> 02:55.608
I'm knackered.

02:55.700 --> 02:59.056
Try sleeping next to the heffalump over there.
Then see how knackered you are.

02:59.140 --> 03:01.051
I'm cookin' a baby.

03:01.140 --> 03:03.859
Which forces you to kick the fuck
out of me in me sleep?!

03:03.940 --> 03:05.259
Wake me up for dinner.

03:05.340 --> 03:08.457
Christ, more meat on a butcher's pencil, Carl.

03:08.540 --> 03:09.609
I've got no clean shirts.

03:09.700 --> 03:12.453
Come on, Debs,
I'm seeing Tracey Kelvin later.

03:12.540 --> 03:15.054
We've got two possibilities, then,
haven't we?

03:15.140 --> 03:17.449
Either I've washed, dried and ironed them

03:17.540 --> 03:19.496
and hid 'em somewhere
so you can't find them,

03:19.580 --> 03:23.334
or alternatively, since you should be
able to get off your arse

03:23.420 --> 03:27.333
and wash your own shirts by now,
it's still in the washing basket.

03:27.420 --> 03:29.331
Which do you think it is?

03:29.420 --> 03:33.493
Well, if you didn't stay up
half the night texting your mates,

03:33.580 --> 03:35.616
you might not be so tetchy of a morning!

03:36.660 --> 03:38.332
So did she wash the shirts or not?

